description:
&lt;p&gt;The Healthier Futures Partnership is offering a short-term post to cover a period of maternity leave. The successful applicant will work as part of the Programme Management Office team as a Project Support Officer covering adhoc project support and administration across the range of STP work streams. This is an exciting role to help support the partnership deliver on its ambitions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key responsibilities that the postholder will be required to undertake include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide a high level, comprehensive, efficient and confidential project support service within as part of the Programme Management Office team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To produce regular and adhoc Programme Management documents / reports as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the shared mailboxes to ensure all Programme Management enquiries are dealt with in a timely and efficient manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide admin support such as taking minutes, action notes, risk log updates for various meetings as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be joining a fast-paced and energetic team. If you would like an informal discussion about the role please contact Raj Kular, PMO Lead on: 07584449149 raj.kular@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a fixed term post until June 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date – 23/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date - TBC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
